data.chText: 世界性的；全球各国的；有各国人的；受各国文化影响的
data.enText: containing people of different types or from different countries, and influenced by their culture

data.chText: 国际性的都市 / 度假胜地
这个俱乐部具有世界文化的气氛。
data.enText: The club has a cosmopolitan atmosphere.

data.chText: 接触过许多国家的人（或事物）的；见过世面的；见识广的
data.enText: having or showing a wide experience of people and things from many different countries

data.chText: 真正具有世界眼光的人
data.enText: people with a truly cosmopolitan outlook
a person who has experience of many different parts of the world

data.chText: 她是个真正的四海为家的人。

word_means: 接触过许多国家的人的

means: 接触过许多国家的人(或事物)的

tr: a sophisticated person who has travelled in many countries

example: the shrewdest political and ecumenical comment of our time"- Christopher Morle

tr: composed of people from or at home in many parts of the world
especially not provincial in attitudes or interests
example: his cosmopolitan benevolence impartially extended to all races and to all creeds"- T.B. Macaula
the ancient and cosmopolitan societies of Syria and Egypt
that queer, cosmopolitan, rather sinister crowd found around the Marseilles docks

tr: growing or occurring in many parts of the world

value.def: A cosmopolitan place or society is full of people from many different countries and cultures.

example.ex: London has always been a cosmopolitan city.
example.tran: 伦敦一直是一个国际化都市。

value.tran: 世界性的，国际化的;受各国文化影响的

value.def: Someone who is cosmopolitan has had a lot of contact with people and things from many different countries and as a result is very open to different ideas and ways of doing things.

example.ex: The family are rich, and extremely sophisticated and cosmopolitan.
example.tran: 这家人很富有，老于世故，而且见多识广。

value.tran: 见过世面的;见识广的;开明的
